# TypeScript Conventions

## General

- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections/utilities.
- Prefer `const` over `let`. Never use `var`.
- Use explicit return types on exported functions.
- Avoid `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards.

## React Components

- Functional components only, default export per file.
- Props interface named `{ComponentName}Props`.
- Use ShadCN components from `@/components/ui/` — do not reimplement primitives.
- Colocate component-specific types in the same file.

## Zustand

- Single store: `src/lib/store/gameStore.ts`.
- Access state via selectors: `useGameStore((s) => s.money)`.
- All mutations through named actions defined in the store.
- Never mutate state directly — always use `set()` or `setState()`.

## Imports

- Use `@/*` path alias for all project imports.
- Group: 1) React/Next, 2) external libraries, 3) `@/components`, 4) `@/lib`.
